title: DIARY-Emerging Markets Economic Events to Oct 30
text:
Oct 19 (Reuters) -
For other diaries, please see:

Government debt auctions
Political and general news events
Index of all diaries
Guide to economic indicators
** This Diary is filed daily *** MONDAY, OCTOBER 19 HELSINKI - Global education industry summit (to Oct. 20). OECD Deputy Secretary-General Stefan Kapferer to deliver opening remarks.
TUESDAY, OCTOBER 20 PRAGUE - Czech National Bank board member Pavel Rezabek to speak in Brno CNB subdivision - 0800 GMT. BUDAPEST - Central Bank of Hungary rate-setting meeting. BRASILIA - Central Bank of Brazil holds Monetary Policy Committee Meeting (to Oct. 21). WARSAW - National Bank of Poland holds Monetary Policy Council meeting (Interest rate announcement not expected). KAMPALA - Central bank of Uganda interest rate decision - 1000 GMT. WEDNESDAY, OCTOBER 21 WINDHOEK - Central bank of Namibia holds Monetary Policy Meeting - 1000 GMT. BRASILIA - Central bank of Brazil announces interest rate decision - 2100 GMT. CAPE TOWN - South African Finance Minister Nhlanhla Nene presents his first medium-term budget policy statement to parliament, with the Treasury's latest budget deficit and economic growth projections for the next three years - 1300 GMT. ANKARA - Central Bank of Turkey monetary policy meeting - 1100 GMT. THURSDAY, OCTOBER 22 STELLENBOSCH, South Africa - South African Reserve Bank Governor Lesetja Kganyago speaks at an economic conference - 0640 GMT. JAKARTA - World Bank issues its quarterly economic review for Indonesia - 0200 GMT. FRIDAY, OCTOBER 23 SEOUL - Bank of Korea Governor Lee Ju-yeol to attend an international conference co-hosted by the Bank of Korea and Yonsei University - 0000 GMT. PARIS - Czech National Bank board member Kamil Janacek to attend a conference on "Securitisation: the way forward?". SUNDAY, OCTOBER 25 ABU DHABI - Summit on Global Agenda 2015 (to Oct. 27). MONDAY, OCTOBER 26 JERUSALEM - Bank of Israel announces interest rate decision - 1430 GMT.
TUESDAY, OCTOBER 27 MEXICO CITY - European Central Bank board member Benoit Coeure at Instituto Tecnologico Autonomo de Mexico (ITAM) - 2200 GMT.
WEDNESDAY, OCTOBER 28 ANKARA - Central bank of Turkey releases quarterly inflation report - 0800 GMT. ANKARA - Central bank of Turkey to publish the minutes of October policy meeting - 1200 GMT.
THURSDAY, OCTOBER 29 LONDON - UK finance minister George Osborne meets Brazilian finance minister Joaquim Levy as a part of UK-Brazil Economic and Financial Dialogue. CHISINAU - Central Bank of Moldova holds monetary policy committee meeting. MEXICO CITY - Central Bank of Mexico announces interest rate decision - 1900 GMT.
FRIDAY, OCTOBER 30 MOSCOW - Central Bank of Russia announces interest rate decision - 1100 GMT.
